        "timestamp": "2022-11-15 14:19:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> > \n> > Hi,\n> > I think there are more things to change to support http instead of https.\n> > Currently the Server only supports https, as I see it.\n> > e.g. in the resources/server.xml there is a connector defined:\n> >     <Connector port=\"8443\" protocol=\"org.apache.coyote.http11.Http11NioProtocol\" maxThreads=\"150\" SSLEnabled=\"true\" scheme=\"https\" secure=\"true\" clientAuth=\"false\" sslProtocol=\"TLS\" keystoreFile=\"{{ .Values.certInitializer.credsPath }}/{{ .Values.certInitializer.fqi_namespace }}.p12\" keystorePass=\"${KEYSTORE_PASSWORD}\" />\n> > \n> > Also in the uui-server/resources/config/application.properties there might be chages required\n> \n> Hi Andreas,\n> So if we want to make it service mesh compatiable, it must support both http and https? Am I right?\n\nNo, the container just needs to provide HTTP, as the ServiceMesh sidecar takes care of the mTLS encryption of the external communication.",
